<div class="highlights">
    <h3 class="highlights__heading">Reporting Highlights</h3>
    <ul class="highlights__list">
                    <li class="highlights__highlight"><span class="highlights__subheading">The Ohio Model: </span> Rarely seen letters show how the voucher movement started in the 1990s as a concealed effort to finance urban parochial schools and expanded to a much broader push.</li>
            <li class="highlights__highlight"><span class="highlights__subheading">Helping the Affluent: </span> An initiative promoted as a civil rights cause — helping poor kids — is increasingly funneling money to families who already easily afford private school tuition.</li>
            <li class="highlights__highlight"><span class="highlights__subheading">The Voucher Deficit: </span> Expanding programs threaten funding for public schools and put pressure on state budgets, as many religious-based schools enjoy new largesse.</li>
            </ul>
    <p class="highlights__disclaimer">
        These highlights were written by the reporters and editors who worked on this story. <span id="survey-placeholder"></span>
    </p>
</div>

